        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 16 at 3:47AM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 346 AM CDT, strong thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 5 miles southwest of Lake Isabel to 12 miles south of
Streeter to 14 miles northwest of Spring Creek Colony.
Movement was northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Steele, Kulm, Gackle, Medina, Tappen, Streeter, Cleveland, Lehr, Jud,
Dawson, Forbes, Lake Isabel, Merricourt City, Windsor, Fredonia,
Crystal Springs, Merricourt, Nortonville, Alfred, and Streeter
Memorial.
</description>
        <instruction>Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CDT for
south central and southeastern North Dakota.</instruction>
